 historians and literary scholars. This interdisciplinary approach focused on the factors, spaces, figures and voices involved in anti-Jewish (and hence anti-Semitic) discourse, both in their historical context and in their literary representation. On the latter issue, as much attention is given to the apologetic as to the critical aspect.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Spanish, Castilian.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 4aAntisemitismus. 4aSpanien. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aAlbert, Mechthild, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAmrán, Rica, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAmselem-Szende, Line, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAponte, Yolanda Montalvo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBachoud, Andrée, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerdah, Jean-François, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBriesemeister, Dietrich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrotons, María Jesús Beltrán, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrown, Kenneth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCardaillac-Hermosilla, Yvette, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChillida, Gonzalo Álvarez, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aContreras Contreras, Jaime, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCortés, Carolina Pizarro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDomergue, Lucienne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGuereña, Jean-Louis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJoan i Tous, Pere, eedito